   "source": [
    "Optimización de modelos de regresión\n",

    "\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Descripción del problema"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Se tienen los resultados de un experimento que relacionan las variables $x$  y  $y$, a partir de los cuales se desea derivar un modelo para pronosticar $d$ en función de nuevos valores de $x$. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Se desean encontra los parámetros $w_0$ y $w_1$ del siguiente modelo de regresión entre las variables $x$ y $y$:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ y = w_1 x + w_0 + e$$\n",
    "\n",
    "a partir de la siguiente tabla de observaciones, donde $d$ es el valor real, $y$ es su aproximación usando el modelo de regresión descrito, y $e$ es el error."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = [0.1087,  0.2698,  0.3765,  0.2146,  0.9155,  \n",
    "     0.0246,  0.0221,  0.8632,  0.6460,  0.2092,  \n",
    "     0.8567,  0.1591,  0.9647,  0.6231,  0.7460,  \n",
    "     0.3654,  0.3065,  0.6886,  0.4966,  0.2008,  \n",
    "     0.2618,  0.7607,  0.1563,  0.4424,  0.7731]\n",
    "\n",
    "d = [0.9519,  1.1237,  1.2360,  1.0526,  2.0743,\n",
    "     0.7906,  0.7603,  2.0533,  1.6887,  1.0563,\n",
    "     2.0991,  0.8953,  2.1917,  1.6266,  1.8508,\n",
    "     1.2828,  1.2283,  1.8722,  1.4657,  1.0418,\n",
    "     1.1097,  1.7826,  0.9711,  1.4267,  1.8248]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Definición del problema matemático "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En un modelo de regresión se desean encontrar los parámetros $w_0$ y $w_1$ de la recta \n",
    "\n",
    "$$y_i = w_0 + w_1 * x_i$$\n",
    "\n",
    "que minimicen la suma de los errores cuadráticos entre el valor real $d_i$ y el valor pronósticado $y_i$ para cada valor posible de la variable $x_i$, tal como se ilustra en la gráfica de abajo. El error $e_i$ se define como $d_i - y_i$.  \n",
    "\n",
    "![reg](assets/sdg-1.jpg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Esto es, se desea encontrar la combinación de parámetros $w_0$ y $w_1$ que minimice:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\text{SSE} = \\sum_i (d_i - y_i)^2 = \\sum_i (d_i - w_0 - w_1 x_i)^2 $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note que en la ecuación anterior, los valores de $x_i$ y $d_i$ son constantes que corresponden a la tabla de datos presentada en la formulación del problema, mientras que las variables son $w_0$ y $w_1$, de tal forma que:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{SSE}(w_0, w_1) = \\sum_i (d_i - w_0 - w_1 x_i)^2 $$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Implementación de la función de pérdida"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "La ecuación anterior (SSE) retorna la suma del error cuadrático para diferentes valores de $w_0$ y $w_1$, calculada sobre el conjunto de datos existentes. Su implementación computacional es la siguiente: "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Sumatoria del error cuadrático\n",
    "##\n",
    "def SSE(w0, w1):\n",
    "    return (sum( [(v - w0 - w1*u)**2  for u, v in zip(x, d)] ))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Forma de la superficie de error (SSE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Ya que la función SSE depende únicamente de los valores de $w_0$ y $w_1$, es posible graficar su forma."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Preparación\n",
    "## \n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib import cm\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "## Generación de una malla de puntos \n",
    "## y valor del SSE en cada punto\n",
    "##\n",
    "W0 = np.arange(-0.5, 3.0, 0.05)\n",
    "W1 = np.arange(-0.5, 3.0, 0.05)\n",
    "W0, W1 = np.meshgrid(W0, W1)\n",
    "F = SSE(W0, W1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "##  Superficie de error\n",
    "##\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')\n",
    "surf = ax.plot_surface(W0, W1, F, cmap=cm.coolwarm, linewidth=1, antialiased=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Contorno\n",
    "##\n",
    "def plot_contour():\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "    ax.set_aspect('equal', 'box')\n",
    "    ax.contour(W0, W1, F, levels=[0, 1, 2, 3, 5, 10, 20, 40, 60, 90])\n",
    "    ax.grid()\n",
    "    \n",
    "plot_contour()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En términos de optimización, se desea encontrar las coordenadas $(w_0, w_1)$ del punto más bajo (error mínimo) de la superficie de error."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Minimización numérica"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Para realizar la optimización numérica de la función $\\text{SSE}(w_0, w_1)$ se utiliza el método del gradiente descendente. Para iniciar, los parámetros $w_0$ y $w_1$ se agrupan en el vector de parámetros $\\mathbf{w}=[w_0, w_1]'$, tal que:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{SSE}(w_0, w_1) = \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w})$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Ahora, como el método es iterativo, se parte de un vector de valores aleatorios, el cual es mejorado en cada iteración, de tal forma que con los valores de $\\mathbf{w}$ en la iteración $k$, $\\mathbf{w}_k$ se obtienen a partir de los valores en la iteración $k-1$ como:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$\n",
    "\n",
    "donde $\\mu$ se define como el tamaño de paso o coeficiente de aprendizaje. Note que\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  w_0\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  w_1\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]_k\n",
    "=\n",
    "\\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  w_{0,k}\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  w_{1,k}\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Gradiente algebraico"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "El gradiente de la función de error se calcula como:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1}) = \n",
    "\\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  \\sum_i \\frac{d}{d w_0} [d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1,k-1} x_i]^2\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  \\sum_i \\frac{d}{d w_1} [d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1,k-1} x_i]^2\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]\n",
    "=\n",
    "\\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  \\sum_i 2 [d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1,k-1} x_i](-1)\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  \\sum_i 2 [d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1,k-1} x_i] (-x_i)\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Si se tiene en cuenta que $e_{i,k-1} = d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1,k-1} x_i$, entonces:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}) = \n",
    "\\left[\n",
    "  \\begin{array}{c}\n",
    "  -2 \\sum_i  e_{i,k-1}\n",
    "  \\\\\n",
    "  -2 \\sum_i  e_{i,k-1} x_i\n",
    "  \\end{array}\n",
    "\\right]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "De esta forma, la función que computa el gradiente se implementa como:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gSSE(w0, w1):\n",
    "    ## calcula el vector de errores\n",
    "    e = [(v - w0 - w1*u)  for u, v in zip(x, d)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## gradientes\n",
    "    gw0 = -2 * sum(e)\n",
    "    gw1 = -2 * sum([q*v for q, v in zip(e,x)])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return (gw0, gw1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Proceso iterativo de mejora de los pesos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A partir de las definiciones y cómputos anteriores, es posible implementar el proceso iterativo de mejora de los pesos usando la ecuación:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def mejora(w0, w1, mu):\n",
    "    ## computa el gradiente para los parámetros actuales\n",
    "    gw0, gw1 = gSSE(w0, w1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## realiza la corrección de los parámetros\n",
    "    w0 = w0 - mu * gw0\n",
    "    w1 = w1 - mu * gw1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## retorna los parámetros corregidos\n",
    "    return (w0, w1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Optimización numérica usando el gradiente"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Para realizar la optimización numérica, se parte de unos pesos iniciales aleatorios. Para efectos ilustrativos se supondra que $w_0 = w_1 = 2.5$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Valores encontrados\n",
      "\n",
      "  w0 = 0.675531\n",
      "  w1 = 1.643269\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "## Punto de inicio\n",
    "w0 = 0.5\n",
    "w1 = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "history_w0 = [w0]\n",
    "history_w1 = [w1]\n",
    "history_f  = [SSE(w0, w1)]\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(20):\n",
    "    w0, w1 = mejora(w0, w1, 0.03)\n",
    "    history_w0.append(w0)\n",
    "    history_w1.append(w1)\n",
    "    history_f.append(SSE(w0, w1))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nValores encontrados\\n\\n  w0 = {:f}\\n  w1 = {:f}'.format(w0, w1))    \n",
    "    \n",
    "plot_contour()\n",
    "plt.plot(history_w0, history_w1, color='red');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},

     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(history_f, '-'); plt.grid()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "##  A continuación se grafican la recta encontrada.\n",
    "##\n",
    "\n",
    "##  Se generan los puntos\n",
    "z = np.linspace(0.0, 1.0)\n",
    "y = w0 + w1 * z\n",
    "\n",
    "## se grafican los datos originales\n",
    "plt.plot(x, d, 'o');\n",
    "\n",
    "## se grafica la recta encontrada\n",
    "plt.plot(z, y, '-');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Aprendizaje Batch vs Aprendizaje Online"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "En aprendizaje de máquinas, el término *Batch* se refiere a que los parámetros del modelo son actualizados con base a una corrección neta computada sobre el conjunto de datos de entrenamiento; este es el caso presentado en este documento, para el cual \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\mathbf{w}_k \n",
    "  = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} \\text{SSE}(\\mathbf{w}_{k-1})\n",
    "  = \\mathbf{w}_{k-1} - \\mu  \\sum_i \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} (d_i - w_{0,k-1} - w_{1, k-1} x_i)^2 \n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Sin embargo, el algoritmo del gradiente también puede ser usado sobre el error instantáneo $e_{i,k}(w_{0,i,k}, w_{1,i,k}) = d_i - w_{0,i,k-1} - w_{1,i,k-1}$ que es una función dependiente del vector $\\mathbf{w}$. De esta forma, la correción de los parámetros se realizar por cada patrón o ejemplo $i$:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathbf{w}_{i,k} \n",
    "  = \\mathbf{w}_{i,k-1} - \\mu \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\mathbf{w}} e_{i,k-1}^2(\\mathbf{w}_{i, k-1})\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "La ecuación anterior simplemente significa que se computa la corrección para un patrón o ejemplo $i$ para los parámetros actuales; luego, se se actualizan los parámetros, y se procede a presentar otro patrón a la red.  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Valores encontrados\n",
      "\n",
      "  w0 = 0.654250\n",
      "  w1 = 1.642800\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x504 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "##\n",
    "## Datos\n",
    "##\n",
    "x = [0.1087,  0.2698,  0.3765,  0.2146,  0.9155,  \n",
    "     0.0246,  0.0221,  0.8632,  0.6460,  0.2092,  \n",
    "     0.8567,  0.1591,  0.9647,  0.6231,  0.7460,  \n",
    "     0.3654,  0.3065,  0.6886,  0.4966,  0.2008,  \n",
    "     0.2618,  0.7607,  0.1563,  0.4424,  0.7731]\n",
    "\n",
    "d = [0.9519,  1.1237,  1.2360,  1.0526,  2.0743,\n",
    "     0.7906,  0.7603,  2.0533,  1.6887,  1.0563,\n",
    "     2.0991,  0.8953,  2.1917,  1.6266,  1.8508,\n",
    "     1.2828,  1.2283,  1.8722,  1.4657,  1.0418,\n",
    "     1.1097,  1.7826,  0.9711,  1.4267,  1.8248]\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "##  Calcula el gradiente para el punto actual (u, v)\n",
    "##\n",
    "def gOnline(u, v, w0, w1):\n",
    "    ## calcula el vector de errores\n",
    "    e = v - w0 - w1*u\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## gradientes\n",
    "    gw0 = -2 * e\n",
    "    gw1 = -2 * e * u\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return (gw0, gw1)\n",
    "\n",
    "def mejora(u, v, w0, w1, mu):\n",
    "    ## computa el gradiente para los parámetros actuales\n",
    "    gw0, gw1 = gOnline(u, v, w0, w1)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## realiza la corrección de los parámetros\n",
    "    w0 = w0 - mu * gw0\n",
    "    w1 = w1 - mu * gw1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ## retorna los parámetros corregidos\n",
    "    return (w0, w1)\n",
    "\n",
    "##\n",
    "## Punto de inicio\n",
    "##\n",
    "w0 = 0.5\n",
    "w1 = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "history_w0 = []\n",
    "history_w1 = []\n",
    "history_f = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for epoch in range(20):\n",
    "    for u, v in zip(x, d):\n",
    "        w0, w1 = mejora(u, v, w0, w1, 0.03)\n",
    "        history_w0.append(w0)\n",
    "        history_w1.append(w1)\n",
    "        history_f.append((v - w0 - w1*u)**2)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\\nValores encontrados\\n\\n  w0 = {:f}\\n  w1 = {:f}'.format(w0, w1))    \n",
    "    \n",
    "plot_contour()\n",
    "plt.plot(history_w0, history_w1, color='red');"
   ]
  },
  {

    "plt.plot(history_f, color='red');"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Gradiente Descendente Estocástico"
   ]
